    summary: "HKU Department of ArchitectureSpring 2025 Discussion SeriesTitle:	The Prism and The MirrorDate:	Marc...",
    description: "HKU Department of ArchitectureSpring 2025 Discussion SeriesTitle:	The Prism and The MirrorDate:	March 28, 2025 (Fri)Time:	12:30-14:00Venue:	 KB719, Knowles Building, The University of Hong KongSpeaker:Marina Montresor Studio Respondents:Thomas Tsang, Associate Dean (Impacts and Communications) and Associate Professor, HKU Guillaume Othenin-Girard, Assistant Professor, HKUChiara Oggioni, Lecturer, HKU Yi Sun, Lecturer, HKU Abstract:The core of the practice lies in the deliberate exploration of architectures broadest spectrum of possibilities, operating across various complementary fields  building, curating, publishing, teaching, and writing. This lecture will showcase the studios distinctive modus operandi by presenting a series of interrelated projects: the renovation of an Art Nouveau villa on Lake Garda (Italy); C/O BARDI, a research and art residency programme; two books by its in-house publishing platform, EDIZIONI C/O BARDI; the teaching programme developed over the past two years at Syracuse University in Florence; and a chapter from Marina Montresors ongoing PhD thesis, Synecdoche, Los Angeles (developed at the ETH Zurich and the Getty Research Institute). Together, these diverse initiatives articulate an understanding of architecture as an inherently generalist discipline  collaborative at its core, adaptable to different challenges, and always engaged in thinking and acting through space. Functioning as both a prism and a mirror, the studio aims to reflect and transform its given context  whether physical, legal, political, or cultural  operating within an ever-changing landscape of possibilities.Biography:Marina Montresor is an architect by training, an artistic director by choice, and a writer by necessity. These three realms converge in her doctoral thesis, Synecdoche, Los Angeles (ETH Zurich, Getty Research Institute), as well as in the architectural and curatorial projects she undertakes with her studio. Alongside her practice, Marina teaches the diploma unit for the Charbonnet-Heiz Chair at ETH Zurich and lectures at Syracuse University in Florence. In 2022, she was a guest professor at TU Wien. She edited the book Defining Criteria (Quart Verlag) in 2018 and will publish the photobooks Calcio Storico by Zara Pfeifer and Postcards from Florence by Louis de Belle and Joris Kritis (EDIZIONI C/O BARDI) in 2025. In 2023, Marina founded the research project C/O BARDI, along with its publishing platform, EDIZIONI C/O BARDI. Based in a 600-year-old Florentine home, C/O BARDI curates art residencies that materialise as printed matter, artist editions, exhibitions, and performances.------------------------------Enquiry: arcevent@hku.hk  All lectures are open to the general public. Seats are available on a first-come, first-served basis and no prior reservation is in need.If you wish to add the Lecture Series to your Google calendar, please select the following link: https://bit.ly/3Hd9QIgRemark: By default, shared calendars wont show up on smartphones. In order to change these settings, you must click on the following link and turn on the HKU Lecture Series calendar:      https://calendar.google.com/calendar/syncselect Date/Time28/03/202512:30-14:00VenueKB719LanguageEnglish",
