    summary: "The Centre of Urban Studies and Urban Planning is pleased to invite you to the CUSUP Research Semina...",
    description: "The Centre of Urban Studies and Urban Planning is pleased to invite you to the CUSUP Research Seminar that will be held on 28 March 2025 (Friday), 13:00 to 14:00 at KB829, 8/F., Knowles Building, HKU. Please be ready 15 minutes prior to the scheduled time.*Pre-registration required.  [Deadline: 27 March 2025 (Thursday) 12:00 noon (HKT)] Registration: https://hkuems1.hku.hk/hkuems/ec_hdetail.aspx?guest=Y&ueid=99394Topic: Regional Policy: Theory and PracticeSpeaker:Professor Ugo FratesiProfessor of Regional Economics and Policy Politecnico di MilanoSchedule: Date: 28 March 2025 (Friday)Time: 13:00-14:00Venue: KB829, 8/F., Knowles Building, HKUAbstract: Regional policy is an essential in any governments toolkit for promoting socioeconomic prosperity. It comes in many forms and can be used to target the development of weak and stronger regions. This seminar presents a new book which provides comprehensive and systematic coverage of regional policy, dealing with core theories and looking at contemporary challenges in practice, addressing regional policy across the world.The presentation focuses on the new definition of regional policy, what it is and what interactions exist between regional policies and other types of policies. Furthermore, the presentation highlights the academic choices behind the structure of the book. Four main topics, each corresponding with a part of the book, have been identified. First, an exploration of regional policys characterisation, aims and rationale. Second, the issues of implementation and the instruments available to policymakers for intervention. Third, regional policy evaluation, as well as statistics and modelling in policymaking. Finally, a discussion of how regional policy is applied in different contexts.About the Speaker:Professor Ugo Fratesi is Professor of Regional Economics and Policy at Politecnico di Milano, Italy. He is Editor-in-Chief of Spatial Economic Analysis. Previously, for eight years, he was Editor of main section papers and Book Review Editor of Regional Studies and, for five years, of the Italian Journal of Regional Science. He is author of a textbook: Regional Policy: Theory and Practice, published by Routledge. He is also author of academic books and articles published in refereed journals in the field of regional economics and policy, primarily on the themes of regional growth and development, policy assessment, cohesion policy, territorial capital, the models for forecasting regional growth, the theory and measurement of regional disparities, the territorial aspects of human capital and innovation. He has been involved with various roles in a large number of research projects, especially at European level, financed by the ESPON, FP5, FP7, Horizon and PRIN programmes, or the European Commission directly.~~ ALL INTERESTED ARE WELCOME ~~Enquiries: 3917 2721CENTRE OF URBAN STUDIES AND URBAN PLANNINGTHE UNIVERSITY OF HONG KONG Date/Time28/03/202513:00-14:00VenueKB829LanguageEnglish",
